Yes, the allocation is fine:
```
set_option trace.compiler.ir.result true in
def foo (x : Array Nat) := 
  x.toVector.size
```
prints
```
[result]
def Mathlib.Meta.FunProp.foo (x_1 : @& obj) : obj :=
  let x_2 : obj := Array.size ‚óæ x_1;
  ret x_2
def Mathlib.Meta.FunProp.foo._boxed (x_1 : obj) : obj :=
  let x_2 : obj := Mathlib.Meta.FunProp.foo x_1;
  dec x_1;
  ret x_2
```
(ie it disappears by the time we get to compiled code).
